The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Spruce-up for Obama
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Spruce-up for Obama
                                          
	Parliaments Central Hall has been closed for renovation before the visit of US President Barack Obama. Obama will address a joint sitting of Parliament in the Central Hall on November 8.         
	The halls blue dome is being repainted and additional lights are being fitted. Giant fans with wide blades, relics of the Constituent Assembly, are also getting a fresh coat of paint.        
	Around 50 artists have been requisitioned to touch up the century-old paintings in the hall.                  
	The winter session of Parliament has been advanced to November 9, primarily to ensure full attendance of MPs at Obamas address. This session will continue till December 13.        
	Over 200 US Secret Service agents are in Delhi. Obama will be the second US President after Bill Clinton to address Indian parliamentarians in the Central Hall. (Picture right shows Clinton during the address in 2000). The same honour was not bestowed upon George W. Bush when he visited India in 2006. Instead, Bush delivered a public speech under the shade of the Purana Qila.                                                                                                                                                           
